015). \"The President and the Apprentice: Eisenhower and Nixon, 1952–1961.\" New Haven, CT: Yale University Press.\nBULLET::::- Greenstein, Fred I. (1991). \"The Hidden-Hand Presidency: Eisenhower as Leader\". Basic Books.\nBULLET::::- Harris, Douglas B. \"Dwight Eisenhower and the New Deal: The Politics of Preemption\", \"Presidential Studies Quarterly\", Vol. 27, 1997.\nBULLET::::- Harris, Seymour E. (1962). \"The Economics of the Political Parties, with Special Attention to Presidents Eisenhower and Kennedy\".\nBULLET::::- Lasby, Clarence G. \"Eisenhower's Heart Attack: How Ike Beat Heart Disease and Held on to the Presidency\" (1997)\nBULLET::::- Medhurst, Martin J. (1993). \"Dwight D. Eisenhower: Strategic Communicator.\" Westport, CT: Greenwood Press.\nBULLET::::- Mayer, Michael S. (2009). \"The Eisenhower Years\" Facts on File.\nBULLET::::- Newton, Jim. (2011) \"Eisenhower: The White House Years\"\nBULLET::::- Pach, Chester J., and Richardson, Elmo (1991). \"Presidency of Dwight D. Eisenhower\". University Press of Kansas.\nBULLET::::- Watry, David M. (2014). \"Diplomacy at the Brink: Eisenhower, Churchill and Eden in the Cold War.\" Baton Rouge, LA: Louisiana State University Press.\n\nBULLET::::- Boyle, Peter G., ed. (1990). \"The Churchill–Eisenhower Correspondence, 1953–1955\". University of North Carolina Press.\nBULLET::::- Boyle, Peter G., ed. (2005). \"The Eden–Eisenhower correspondence, 1955–1957\". University of North Carolina Press.\nBULLET::::- Butcher, Harry C. (1946). \"My Three Years With Eisenhower The Personal Diary of Captain Harry C. Butcher, USNR\", candid memoir by a top aide\nBULLET::::- Eisenhower, Dwight D. (1948). \"Crusade in Europe\", his war memoirs.\nBULLET::::- Eisenhower, Dwight D. (1965). \"The White House Years: Waging Peace 1956–1961\", Doubleday and Co.\nBULLET::::- \"Eisenhower Papers\" 21-volume scholarly edition; complete for 1940–1961.\nBULLET::::- Summersby, Kay (1948). \"Eisenhower was My Boss\", New York: Prentice Hal