car II of Sweden (b. 1829)\nBULLET::::- 1913 – Camille Jenatzy, Belgian race car driver (b. 1868)\nBULLET::::- 1914 – Melchior Anderegg, Swiss mountain guide (b. 1828)\nBULLET::::- 1914 – Maximilian von Spee, Danish-German admiral (b. 1861)\nBULLET::::- 1917 – Mendele Mocher Sforim, Russian author (b. 1836)\nBULLET::::- 1918 – Josip Štadler, Croatian archbishop (b. 1843)\nBULLET::::- 1919 – J. Alden Weir, American painter (b. 1852)\nBULLET::::- 1929 – José Vicente Concha, Columbian politician and 8th President of Colombia (b. 1867)\nBULLET::::- 1937 – Hans Molisch, Czech-Austrian botanist and academic (b. 1856)\nBULLET::::- 1938 – Friedrich Glauser, Swiss author (b. 1896)\nBULLET::::- 1940 – George Lloyd, English-Canadian bishop and theologian (b. 1861)\nBULLET::::- 1942 – Albert Kahn, American architect, Fisher Building, Packard Automotive Plant, Ford River Rouge Complex (b. 1869)\nBULLET::::- 1952 – Charles Lightoller, English sailor (b. 1874)\nBULLET::::- 1954 – Claude Cahun, French artist, photographer, and writer (b. 1894)\nBULLET::::- 1954 – Gladys George, American actress (b. 1904)\nBULLET::::- 1954 – Joseph B. Keenan, American lawyer and politician (b. 1888)\nBULLET::::- 1958 – Tris Speaker, American baseball player and manager (b. 1888)\nBULLET::::- 1963 – Sarit Thanarat, Thai field marshal and politician, 11th Prime Minister of Thailand (b. 1908)\nBULLET::::- 1966 – Ward Morehouse, American playwright, author, and critic (b. 1899)\nBULLET::::- 1971 – Ernst Krenkel, Russian geographer and explorer (b. 1903)\nBULLET::::- 1971 – Eleni Ourani, Greek poet and critic (b. 1896)\nBULLET::::- 1975 – Gary Thain, New Zealand bass player (b. 1948)\nBULLET::::- 1978 – Golda Meir, Ukrainian-Israeli educator and politician, 4th Prime Minister of Israel (b. 1898)\nBULLET::::- 1980 – John Lennon, English singer-songwriter and guitarist (b. 1940)\nBULLET::::- 1982 – Bram Behr, Surinamese journalist and politician (b. 1951)\nBULLET::::- 1982 – André Kamperveen, Surinamese fo