pe Panneton, Canadian physician, academic, and diplomat (b. 1895)\nBULLET::::- 1963 – Paul Hindemith, German violinist, composer, and conductor (b. 1895)\nBULLET::::- 1967 – Katharine McCormick, American biologist and philanthropist (b. 1875)\nBULLET::::- 1968 – David Ogilvy, 12th Earl of Airlie, Scottish peer, soldier and courtier (b. 1893)\nBULLET::::- 1971 – Max Steiner, Austrian-American pianist, composer, and conductor (b. 1888)\nBULLET::::- 1976 – Katharine Byron, American politician (b. 1903)\nBULLET::::- 1981 – Allan Dwan, Canadian-American director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1885)\nBULLET::::- 1983 – William Demarest, American actor (b. 1892)\nBULLET::::- 1983 – Dennis Wilson, American drummer, songwriter, and producer (b. 1944)\nBULLET::::- 1984 – Sam Peckinpah, American director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1925)\nBULLET::::- 1984 – Mary Stewart, Baroness Stewart of Alvechurch, British politician and educator (b. 1903)\nBULLET::::- 1986 – John D. MacDonald, American colonel and author (b. 1916)\nBULLET::::- 1986 – Jan Nieuwenhuys, Dutch painter (b. 1922)\nBULLET::::- 1989 – Hermann Oberth, Romanian-German physicist and engineer (b. 1894)\nBULLET::::- 1990 – Warren Skaaren, American screenwriter and producer (b. 1946)\nBULLET::::- 1992 – Sal Maglie, American baseball player and coach (b. 1917)\nBULLET::::- 1993 – William L. Shirer, American journalist and historian (b. 1904)\nBULLET::::- 1994 – Jean-Louis Lévesque, Canadian businessman and philanthropist (b. 1911)\nBULLET::::- 1999 – Clayton Moore, American actor (b. 1914)\nBULLET::::- 2001 – Samuel Abraham Goldblith, American lieutenant, biologist, and engineer (b. 1919)\nBULLET::::- 2001 – William X. Kienzle, American priest and author (b. 1928)\nBULLET::::- 2003 – Benjamin Thurman Hacker, American admiral (b. 1935)\nBULLET::::- 2004 – Jerry Orbach, American actor and singer (b. 1935)\nBULLET::::- 2004 – Susan Sontag, American novelist, essayist, critic, and playwright (b. 1933)\nBULLET::::- 2006