que\" (1782)\n\nBULLET::::- Contributions to liberal theory\nBULLET::::- Diderot effect\nBULLET::::- Encyclopedist\nBULLET::::- Encyclopédistes\nBULLET::::- Euler, Leonhard\nBULLET::::- List of liberal theorists\nBULLET::::- Society of the Friends of Truth\nBULLET::::- Paris Diderot University\nBULLET::::- Denis Diderot House of Enlightenment\n\nBULLET::::- Anderson, Wilda C. \"Diderot's Dream.\" Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press, 1990.\nBULLET::::- App, Urs (2010). \"The Birth of Orientalism\". Philadelphia: University of Pennsylvania Press, , pp. 133–87 on Diderot's role in the European discovery of Hinduism and Buddhism.\nBULLET::::- Azurmendi, Joxe (1984). Entretien d'un philosophe: Diderot (1713–1784), \"Jakin\", 32: 111–21.\nBULLET::::- Ballstadt, Kurt P.A. \"Diderot: Natural Philosopher.\" Oxford: Voltaire Foundation, 2008.\nBULLET::::- Blom, Philipp (2010). \"The Wicked Company\". New York: Basic Books\nBULLET::::- Blum, Carol (1974). \"Diderot: The Virtue of a Philosopher\"\nBULLET::::- Brewer, Daniel. \"Using the Encyclopédie: Ways of Knowing, Ways of Reading.\" Oxford: Voltaire Foundation, 2002.\nBULLET::::- Clark, Andrew Herrick. \"Diderot's Part.\" Aldershot, Hampshire, England: Ashgate, 2008.\nBULLET::::- Caplan, Jay. \"Framed Narratives: Diderot's Genealogy of the Beholder.\" Manchester: Manchester UP, 1986.\nBULLET::::- Crocker, Lester G. (1974). \"Diderot's Chaotic Order: Approach to a Synthesis\"\nBULLET::::- Curran, Andrew S. (2019). \"Diderot and the Art of Thinking Freely\"\nBULLET::::- De la Carrera, Rosalina. \"Success in Circuit Lies: Diderot's Communicational Practice.\" Stanford, CA: Stanford UP, 1991.\nBULLET::::- Dlugach, Tamara. \"Denis Diderot\". Moscow: Progress Publishers. 1988.\nBULLET::::- Fellows, Otis E. (1989). \"Diderot\"\nBULLET::::- France, Peter (1983). \"Diderot\"\nBULLET::::- Fontenay, Elisabeth de, and Jacques Proust. \"Interpréter Diderot Aujourd'hui.\" Paris: Le Sycomore, 1984.\nBULLET::::- Furbank, P.N. (1992). 